# Async/await preference

## General rule

Prefer **async/await** over **.then()** for async work. Use `.then()` only when necessary (e.g. returning a promise without awaiting, or chaining in a way that is clearer than async/await).

```typescript
// ❌ BAD – .then() when async/await is clearer
getCandidateById(candidateId)
  .then(profile => { if (!cancelled) setCandidate(profile); })
  .catch(() => { if (!cancelled) setError('Failed'); })
  .finally(() => { if (!cancelled) setIsLoading(false); });

// ✅ GOOD – async/await
const profile = await getCandidateById(candidateId);
if (!cancelled) setCandidate(profile);
```

## React hooks (useEffect, etc.)

Inside a React hook, **do not** make the effect callback async. Define an **async function inside** the effect, use **try/catch/finally**, then **call** that function.

Pattern (see `src/app/(authenticated)/_components/AdminDashboard.tsx`):

1. Declare an async function inside the effect (e.g. `const fetchData = async () => { ... }`).
2. In the function: set loading/clear error, **await** your calls (e.g. `await Promise.allSettled([...])`), handle results, then in **finally** clear loading.
3. Call the function at the end of the effect (e.g. `fetchData()`).

```typescript
// ❌ BAD – effect callback async or .then in effect
useEffect(() => {
  getData(id).then(setData).catch(setError).finally(() => setIsLoading(false));
}, [id]);

// ✅ GOOD – inner async function + call
useEffect(() => {
  const fetchData = async () => {
    try {
      setIsLoading(true);
      clearError('data');
      const [result] = await Promise.allSettled([getData(id)]);
      handleResult(result, setData, 'data');
    } catch (err) {
      console.error('Error fetching data:', err);
      setError('data', 'Failed to load');
    } finally {
      setIsLoading(false);
    }
  };
  fetchData();
}, [id, handleResult, clearError, setError]);
```

Use **cancellation** (e.g. `let cancelled = false; return () => { cancelled = true; };`) when the effect can re-run before the previous fetch finishes, so you don’t update state after unmount or with stale deps.
